{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":53574,"duration_api_ms":53536,"num_turns":13,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"6eb0fa95-86e0-4ee3-89f3-f00e6b2de968","total_cost_usd":0.38689700000000005,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":29578,"cache_read_input_tokens":285219,"output_tokens":2375,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":29578,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":10,"outputTokens":2375,"cacheReadInputTokens":285219,"cacheCreationInputTokens":29578,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.38689700000000005,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Both amendments identify genuine correctness defects verified by code inspection. Amendment fr-3-b8dbc656 correctly identifies that lineage sealing before snapshot/journal writes creates an unrecoverable state on partial failure, since no reconciliation path exists. Amendment fr-3-9fecdf73 correctly identifies that bead completion persists a snapshot violating the model's own invariant (Active status with no active_bead), which the model explicitly defines as inconsistent at model.rs:172-176.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-3-b8dbc656","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: `update_task_run` at service.rs:417 seals the lineage entry before `write_snapshot` (line 456) and `append_event` (line 474). `FsTaskRunLineageStore::update_task_run` at fs.rs:2545-2556 hard-rejects re-finalization of already-terminal entries. The doc comment at service.rs:390-393 claims reconciliation can repair the drift ('until reconciled'), but grepping the milestone_record context reveals no reconcile/repair/recover function exists. A transient I/O failure after lineage sealing but before snapshot or journal writes leaves the milestone permanently inconsistent with no automated recovery path. This is a real durability/idempotence defect."},{"amendment_id":"fr-3-9fecdf73","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: `record_bead_start` at service.rs:307-308 promotes status to `MilestoneStatus::Active`. `update_task_run` at service.rs:448-453 clears `active_bead` to `None` when the completing bead matches, but never transitions `status` away from `Active`. `MilestoneSnapshot::validate_semantics` at model.rs:172-176 explicitly rejects `status == Active && active_bead == None` as inconsistent. Unlike `update_status` (service.rs:199-204) which calls `validate_semantics()` before writing, the completion path at service.rs:456 writes the snapshot directly via `write_snapshot` without validation. This means every normal single-bead completion persists a snapshot that violates the model's own invariant. This is a real correctness bug — the invariant check exists precisely to catch this state, but the completion path bypasses it."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"f263125d-1187-420a-b142-6f6d4561540f"}
